summary: This document is a template or explanatory guide from T-Mobile US Inc. detailing the structure and content of subscriber information reports provided in response to legal requests. It outlines the types of data fields included (subscriber, account, device, billing details) and provides contact information for various Mobile Virtual Network Operator (MVNO) partners for directing subpoenas.
keyFacts: The document is a template explaining the format of subscriber data reports provided by T-Mobile in response to legal requests.
It details extensive data fields that can be included, such as subscriber name, address, phone number (MDN/MSISDN), device identifiers (IMEI, ICCID), billing information, and account status.

It lists contact information for numerous MVNO partners (like Kajeet, Google/Nova, Consumer Cellular, Ting, Plintron, Ultra Mobile, Walmart Family Mobile, TracFone, Twilio, LycaMobile) for directing subpoenas, as T-Mobile does not hold subscriber data for these wholesale accounts.
The document references file identifiers EFTA00153459 through EFTA00153463, suggesting it is part of a series of records or a data production.
